  "details": "@monitoring-lib/error-tracking is a dependency-confusion stub (version 9999.0.0, ~530 bytes, no library code) whose preinstall hook collects os.hostname() and os.userInfo().username and exfiltrates them via an HTTPS GET to d8ks495t5p5ut2enft8041g7fusnfsy5e[.]oast[.]site/?h=HOST\u0026u=USER\u0026pkg=..., and simultaneously via a DNS lookup to monitoring-lib[.]HOST.d8ks495t5p5ut2enft8041g7fusnfsy5e[.]oast[.]site — out-of-band host-metadata exfiltration as part of a dependency-confusion supply-chain attack.",
